{meta: title Fraulein}
{meta: artist Bobby Helms}
{meta: composer Lawton Williams}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Far across deep blue waters  lives an old German's [F]daughter
By the [G7]banks of the  old river [C]Rhine
Where I loved her and left her  but I can't forget [F]her
[G7]I miss my pretty [C]Fraulein
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Fraulein  Fraulein  look up toward the [F]Heaven
Each [G7]night when the stars start to [C]shine
By the same stars above you I swear that I love [F]you
[G7]You are my pretty [C]Fraulein
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
When my memories wander away over [F]yonder
To the [G7]sweetheart that I left [C]behind
In a moment of glory a face comes before [F]me
The face of my [G7]pretty [C]Fraulein
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Fraulein Fraulein walk down by the [F]river
[G7]Pretend that your hand's holding [C]mine
By the same stars above you I swear that I love [F]you
[G7]You are my pretty [C]Fraulein
{end_of_verse}
